The paper discusses the application of Genetic Programming to the discovery of empirical laws, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on the problem of intron growth, which is a common issue in machine learning and optimization algorithms, making categories such as Machine Learning (cs.LG), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Software Engineering (cs.SE) likely candidates. Finally, the paper introduces a new program evolution framework, which involves grammar-based genetic programming, making Programming Languages (cs.PL) another possible category.
